<p>
    <strong>AwesomeTTS</strong> brings text-to-speech support to the users
    of <a href="http://ankisrs.net">Anki</a>, with playback support for
    the following services.
</p>

<ul>
    <li>
        <a href="http://www.eguidedog.net/ekho.php">Ekho</a> (requires
        that the <code>ekho</code> binary is installed and available)
    </li>
    <li>
        <a href="http://espeak.sourceforge.net">eSpeak</a> (requires that
        the <code>espeak</code> binary is installed and available)
    </li>
    <li>
        <a href="http://www.cstr.ed.ac.uk/projects/festival">Festival</a>
        (requires Linux and that the <code>festival</code> and
        <code>text2wave</code> binaries are installed and available)
    </li>
    <li>
        Google Translate (requires an Internet connection)
    </li>
    <li>
        Microsoft Speech API, also known as SAPI 5 (requires Windows)
    </li>
    <li>
        OS X Speech Synthesis Manager (requires Mac OS X)
    </li>
</ul>

<h2>Installation</h2>

<p>
    From Anki&rsquo;s main window, go to the <em>Tools</em> menu, then
    select <em>Add-ons</em>, followed by <em>Browse &amp; Install</em>.
    When prompted, enter <code>301952613</code> as the add-on code. Once
    downloaded, restart Anki to enable the add-on.
</p>

